What I'd like to have at the end:

Directory layout:
- src
  - main
    - foo.js
    - bar.js
  - test
    - foo-test.js
    - bar-test.js
  - demo.html
  - demo.js
  - runner.html
- node_modules
  - ...
- data
  - test.txt
- dist
  - main
    - foo.js
    - bar.js
  - bundle.js
  - bundle.min.js
  ✓ test.js
  ✓ demo.html
  ✓ runner.html

- I'd like the test to be able to issue an XHR for /data/test.txt.
- The dev server should update & reload pages.
- Should build a bundle which can be browserified from another repo
  (and include an external sourcemap)
  Should have NODE_ENV=production

To iterate on the demo, run:

    webpack-dev-server --hot --inline --progress --colors

And then load http://localhost:9090/dist/demo.html

To iterate on the tests, run:

    webpack-dev-server --hot --inline --progress --colors

And then load http://localhost:9090/dist/runner.html

To build a "production" bundle, run:

    webpack --config webpack.config.prod.js &&
    webpack --config webpack.config.prod.min.js
